<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Plants which were considered to be hybrids between 
<taxonomicName family="Lamiaceae" genus="Th." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Th. richardii subsp. vigoi" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="subSpecies" species="richardii" subSpecies="vigoi">Th. richardii subsp. vigoi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. piperella" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="piperella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. piperella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. have been called 
<taxonomicName genus="T." isHybrid="true" lsidName="T. bolosii" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="bolosii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
T. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
bolosii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The hybrid has been reported from a small area of Serra de la Safor, eastern Spain (
<bibRefCitation author="Riera, J" journalOrPublisher="Flora Montiberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="77 - 80" refId="B22" refString="Riera, J, Guemes, J, Rossello, JA, 2020. Thymus x bolosii (Lamiaceae) a new wild hybrid from the eastern Iberian Peninsula. Flora Montiberica 78: 77 - 80" title="Thymus x bolosii (Lamiaceae) a new wild hybrid from the eastern Iberian Peninsula." volume="78" year="2020">Riera et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
